title: Tech Sector Breaking Above 17-Year Fibonacci Resistance
text:
Invesco QQQ Trust ETF

This chart looks at tech ETF on a monthly basis over the past 20 years, where Fibonacci extension levels were applied to the 1999 highs at (A) and the 2002 lows at (B).

Last September, the ETF met a ton of selling pressure on its first attempt to break above the 161% level. This selling pressure drove QQQ down nearly 20% into the last week of December.

The rally over the past 10 months has QQQ working on a solid breakout above the 161% level at (1).

If QQQ succeeds in closing the month at the highest monthly closing price in history, it will send a positive message from this sector to the broad markets.
